Data Privacy Framework
Data Privacy Framework Notice
Last Updated: August 12, 2024
Garmin International, Inc., and its U.S.-based affiliates (listed below) comply with the EU-U.S. (including the UK Extension) and Swiss-U.S. Data Privacy Framework ("DPF") principles regarding the collection, use, sharing, and retention of personal data from the European Economic Area ("EEA"), United Kingdom ("U.K."), Gibraltar, and Switzerland as described in our
EU-U.S. DPF certification (including the UK Extension) and Swiss-U.S. DPF certification
.
Learn more about the DPF
.
Detailed information about our processing of personal data, including purposes of processing, third-party recipients, and your rights, can be found in
our privacy policies
. We encourage you to review the privacy policies applicable to the websites, apps, products, and services you use.
Garmin International, Inc. and its U.S.-based affiliates (listed below) are subject to the oversight of the U.S. Federal Trade Commission and remain responsible for personal data transferred to third parties that process it on our behalf. If you have a complaint about our DPF compliance, please contact us at
privacy@garmin.com
. You can also refer a complaint to our chosen independent dispute resolution body,
JAMS
, and, in certain circumstances, invoke the DPF arbitration process.
The following Garmin companies are covered under our DPF certifications:
AeroData, Inc.
AeroNavData, Inc.
Garmin AT, Inc.
Garmin Insurance Services, LLC
Garmin International, Inc.
Garmin Services, Inc.
Garmin USA, Inc.
